<div class="container">

<div class="sheet" id="content">

    <div class="introShow">
      <div class="">
        <h1 style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font1 =%>'" ><%= @guide.title %></h1>

      </div>
      <img id="logo" src="<%= @guide.image.url %>" alt="logo">
      <div class="blurb">
        <p style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>';"><span style="font-weight:bold" class="gray"></span><em><%= @guide.description %></em></p>
        <p style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>';"><span style="font-weight:bold" class="gray">Author:</span> <%= @guide.author %></p>
        <p style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>';"><span style="font-weight:bold" class="gray">Website:</span></p>
        <p style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>';"><span style="font-weight:bold" class="gray">Github:</span> <%= @guide.github %></p>
        <p style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>';"><span style="font-weight:bold" class="gray">Trello:</span> <%= @guide.trello %></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="colourShow" style="border-bottom: 4px solid <%= @guide.colour4 %> ">
      <div id="cc1" style="background-color:<%= @guide.colour1 %>; font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>';" class="circleShow grow"><%= @guide.colour1 %>
        <button class="clipboard-btn" data-clipboard-action="copy" data-clipboard-target="#cc1"></button>
      </div>

      <div  id="cc2" style="background-color:<%= @guide.colour2 %>; font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>'" class="circleShow grow"><%= @guide.colour2 %>
        <button class="clipboard-btn" data-clipboard-action="copy" data-clipboard-target="#cc2"></button>
      </div>
      <div id="cc3" style="background-color:<%= @guide.colour3 %>; font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>'" class="circleShow grow"><%= @guide.colour3 %>
        <button class="clipboard-btn" data-clipboard-action="copy" data-clipboard-target="#cc3"></button>
      </div>
      <div id="cc4" style="background-color:<%= @guide.colour4 %>; font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>'" class="circleShow grow"><%= @guide.colour4 %>
        <button class="clipboard-btn" data-clipboard-action="copy" data-clipboard-target="#cc4"></button>
      </div>
      <div id="colourBlurb" style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>'; border-bottom: 4px solid <%= @guide.colour4 %>"><p><span style="color: <%= @guide.colour1 %> "><%= @guide.colour1 %></span> is <%= @guide.title %>'s main colour. If the thing youâ€™re making has colour, this colour should be in it.</p>
        <p><span style="color: <%= @guide.colour2 %>"><%= @guide.colour2 %></span> is the secondary colour - it may be a good choice for elements that need to stand out. </p>
        <p><span style="color: <%= @guide.colour3 %> "><%= @guide.colour3 %> </span>and <span style="color: <%= @guide.colour4 %> "><%= @guide.colour4 %></span> are tertiary accent colours that should mostly be used in small doses and once the primary colours have been used.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="tonesShow">
      <div style="background-color:<%= @guide.tone2 %>;" class="tshow"></div>
      <div style="background-color:<%= @guide.tone3 %>;" class="tshow"></div>
      <div style="background-color:<%= @guide.tone4 %>;" class="tshow"></div>
      <div style="background-color:<%= @guide.tone5 %>;" class="tshow"></div>
      <div style="background-color:<%= @guide.tone6 %>;" class="tshow"></div>
      <div style="background-color:<%= @guide.tone7 %>;" class="tshow"></div>
    </div>


    <div class="fontShow" style="border-bottom: 4px solid <%= @guide.colour4 %> ">
      <h1 style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font1 =%>';"><%= @guide.font1 =%> </h1>
      <h2 style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font1 =%>';"><%= @guide.font1 =%> </h2>
      <h3 style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font1 =%>';"><%= @guide.font1 =%></h3>
      <h4 style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font1 =%>';"><%= @guide.font1 =%></h4>
      <p style="font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>';"><%= @guide.font2 =%></p>
    </div>

    <div class="codeSnippet">
      <p>To embed your selected fonts into a webpage, copy this code into the head of your HTML document:</p>
      <xmp><link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family="<%= @guide.font1 =%>|<%= @guide.font2 =%>" rel="stylesheet"></xmp>
      <p>Then use the following CSS rules to specify these families:</p>
      <xmp>font-family: '<%= @guide.font1 =%>';</xmp>
      <xmp>font-family: '<%= @guide.font2 =%>';</xmp>

    </div>

  </div>

  </div>

</div>
